Dear all,

At CT2010 in Genova, I gave a talk on numerical invariants of enriched
categories and their applications to measuring diversity.  A paper giving
some background is now available:

    Tom Leinster and Christina Cobbold,
    Measuring diversity: the importance of species similarity.
    _Ecology_, in press.
    http://www.maths.gla.ac.uk/~tl/mdiss.pdf

As the name of the journal suggests, it was written for ecologists - but
it should be accessible to mathematicians too.

Best wishes,
Tom



